# Title
`Nutanix (#NTNX) in 2026: A Compelling Long-Term Investment Despite Recent Downgrades`

# Date
`2026-01-13`

# Tags
- #NTNX
- #NKP
- #HCI

# Content
```md
**References**

*   [GitLab, Nutanix receive downgrades to Equal-weight by Morgan Stanley](https://seekingalpha.com/news/4538463-gitlab-nutanix-receive-downgrades-to-equal-weight-by-morgan-stanley)
    
*   [Q3 2025 Forrester Wave™ for Multicloud Container Platforms](https://reprint.forrester.com/reports/the-forrester-wavetm-multicloud-container-platforms-q3-2025-f7668424/index.html)
    

Recent analyst actions, including Morgan Stanley’s downgrade and target price reduction from $82 to $62 (as of January 12, 2026), appear overly cautious and somewhat conflicting given Nutanix’s (#[NTNX](https://www.google.com/finance/quote/NTNX:NASDAQ)) strong fundamentals and market positioning.

The company boasts a revenue scale exceeding $2.5B annually, operating margins above 20%, and free cash flow margins around 30% — metrics that underscore a highly attractive business model. The [Q3 2025 Forrester Wave™ for Multicloud Container Platforms](https://reprint.forrester.com/reports/the-forrester-wavetm-multicloud-container-platforms-q3-2025-f7668424/index.html) ranks Nutanix (#[NTNX](https://www.google.com/finance/quote/NTNX:NASDAQ)) as a top-tier Leader (among the top 3), highlighting its strengths in Kubernetes capabilities via the 2023 D2iQ acquisition, seamless VM-to-container modernization, edge deployments (including air-gapped environments), and integration with Nutanix (#[NTNX](https://www.google.com/finance/quote/NTNX:NASDAQ)) AHV and AI stack.

[

