(Source: [Q3 2025 Forrester Wave™ for Multicloud Container Platforms](https://reprint.forrester.com/reports/the-forrester-wavetm-multicloud-container-platforms-q3-2025-f7668424/index.html))

Nutanix’s (#[NTNX](https://www.google.com/finance/quote/NTNX:NASDAQ)) founding team brings deep expertise in distributed systems — with co-founder Mohit Aron influenced by work on Google File System — combined with strategic alliances (e.g., Google Cloud for hybrid multicloud) that position it well for VMware migrations, private AI, and edge scenarios.

While near-term revenue timing issues (e.g., Q1 FY2026 miss and guidance adjustment) triggered the pullback, underlying demand remains solid, as evidenced by robust RPO growth and positive Seeking Alpha analyses emphasizing long-term growth, market share gains from VMware, and rising free cash flow.

For reference, here’s a recent Seeking Alpha chart illustrating [NTNX](https://www.google.com/finance/quote/NTNX:NASDAQ) stock performance trends through late 2025 into early 2026, showing the post-earnings dip but highlighting recovery potential:

